    "Name": "SM2 SPG",
    "Details": "LAW produced small quantities of a version of the SM2 that replaced the Sniper Artillery Piece with a larger Long Tom Cannon and twenty-five rounds of ammunition. This variant wasn't a huge success; while the extra range and power of the Long Tom Cannon was a definite advantage, the vehicle suffered from severe structural instability. This instability was a result of poorly-placed shock rings, with the powerful recoil of the Cannon causing it to actually rip free of the mountings on occasion. LAW took a pragmatic approach to the problems with this variant: they offered it for sale at a reduced price.\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>ICE: Air breathing Combustion Engine. This unit can not deploy in thin atmosphere.</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Movement: 3/5 Hex: 90/150 Meters.</color></b>\n\n<color=#ffcc00><b>Armor:</b> Ferro-Fibrous (C)\n<b>Structure:</b> Structure\n<b>Values       A        S  </b>\n<b>Front</b>       460     40\n<b>Left</b>         375     40\n<b>Right</b>       375     40\n<b>Rear</b>        300     40\n\n<b>Total</b>      1510    160</color>\n\n<color=#ff0000>Quirk: Improved Communications</color>",
